OL,3,CTemperatures expected to ease after
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave
OL,6,FWales also set a new national May
OL,7,Frecord on Tuesday, reaching 32.9C in
OL,8,FCardiff, while on Tuesday night, a new
OL,9,Fnighttime record was set in Camborne,
OL,10,FCornwall, with the minimum temperature
OL,11,Ffalling no lower than 21.4C.
OL,13,FOverall, the UK will remain warm from
OL,14,FThursday, particularly in the South,
OL,15,Fwith "some fresher and possibly
OL,16,Fshowery conditions" expected from
OL,17,FFriday into the weekend, the Met
OL,18,FOffice said.
OL,26,@wD@FOUxD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
