OL,3,CTemperatures expected to ease after
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave
OL,6,FThis week's heatwave saw thousands of
OL,7,Fpeople in Kent asked to use water for
OL,8,Fessential purposes only after high
OL,9,Fdemand led to supply issues.
OL,11,FMatthew Dean, South East Water's head
OL,12,Fof operations control, said around
OL,13,F18,000 customers were experiencing a
OL,14,Fwater supply issue, and some would
OL,15,Fhave intermittent supply until
OL,16,Freservoir levels were restored.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1780002672
OL,3,CTemperatures expected to ease after
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heatwave
OL,6,F"We are continuing to ask customers in
OL,7,Fsupply to use water for essential
OL,8,Fpurposes only ` for drinking, washing
OL,9,Fand cooking," he said. "We have
OL,10,Fbottled water collection stations
OL,11,Falready set up and are monitoring."
OL,13,FWhile many people have been enjoying
OL,14,Fthe week's sunny weather, the heatwave
OL,15,Fhas presented hazards, with NHS
OL,16,FEngland saying there were 20,092
OL,17,Fvisits to its heatstroke advice page
OL,18,Fon bank holiday Monday, compared with
OL,19,F488 the previous Monday.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@MO]qD@XOUsD@cO]
